parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, hesitate, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks
hesitates
or fails to accelerate
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the RPMs rev high without increasing speed
the vehicle shudders or vibrates
and the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, such as stalling, loss of motive power, and malfunctioning of various components, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
loss of motive power
malfunctioning of components such as air conditioning
power windows
and seats
and warning lights illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Doors failing to lock or unlock
doors sticking or not closing properly
and warning lights illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power windows can cause safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Power windows failing to operate
windows moving up and down randomly
and windows failing to stay up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs can cause safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Parts not available for recall repairs
excessive wait times for repairs
and vehicles not being repaired in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and safety risks.
symptoms: Air conditioning blowing cold air
malfunctioning of air mix motor control
and expensive repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feeling soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks
loses power
and the brake pedal squeaks; the transmission does not shift gears properly; the vehicle stalls or stops moving; the RPMs rise drastically; the gas pedal does not operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Key fob issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The key fob does not work properly; the alarm system does not function; the vehicle cannot be locked or unlocked; the key fob is deactivated without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear hatchback/power strut issues can cause the hatch to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The rear hatchback does not stay open; the hatch closes suddenly; the hatch does not open or close properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sunroof/window issues can cause the sunroof or window to shatter or malfunction, leading to safety risks and injury.
symptoms: The sunroof explodes or shatters; the rear passenger window implodes; the window does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Recall issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle has an open recall that has not been remedied; the manufacturer does not provide a solution or repair; the vehicle is not safe to drive due to the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air conditioning issues can cause discomfort and safety risks, especially in extreme temperatures.
symptoms: The air conditioning does not work; the air conditioning blows hot air; the fan makes a roaring sound; the temperature cannot be regulated.
